Metadata: The isolation and characterizatio​n of Agardhilactone, a novel oxylipin from the marine red alga "Agardhiella subulata."

A novel tricyclic oxylipin containing delta-lactone, cyclopentane and epoxide rings and a conjugated diene, has been isolated from the marine red alga Agardhiella subulata. The structure, including partial stereochemistry​, was determined by NMR and GC-MS analysis of menthoxycarbony​l derivatives.
